The new Kaizer Cheifs coach is pleased with the facilities at his disposal. Gavin Hunt coached against the Amakhosi team which narrowly missed out on the Premiership title. He is determined to instill a title-winning mentality within his squad. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Kaizer Chiefs confirmed the appointment of former Bidvest Wits coach Gavin Hunt as their new head coach on Thursday. Hunt comes with a wealth of football knowledge and experience, having won the league championship on four occasions, including three successive titles with SuperSport United. READ: Chiefs await transfer ban ruling Hunt says he's determined to instill a title-winning mentality within his squad. He also said that he is pleased with the facilities at his disposal.